---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Contact"
  description="Get in touch with Peter Kolosei — research, collaborations, ulpan inquiries."
>
  <h1>Contact</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Plain email works best. I read everything, reply to what's substantive.
  </p>

  <h2>By purpose</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>General / personal</strong> — <a href="mailto:peter@kolosei.com">peter@kolosei.com</a></li>
    <li><strong>Research, academic, OSF/GeneMatcher-related</strong> — <a href="mailto:research@kolosei.com">research@kolosei.com</a></li>
    <li><strong>LinguistPro</strong> (ulpan students, learners, bug reports) — <a href="mailto:linguistpro@kolosei.com">linguistpro@kolosei.com</a></li>
    <li><strong>EgorGenom case</strong> (clinical, lab, rare-disease colleagues) — <a href="mailto:egor@kolosei.com">egor@kolosei.com</a></li>
    <li><strong>Anything else</strong> — <a href="mailto:hi@kolosei.com">hi@kolosei.com</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p class="small muted">
    All aliases land in the same inbox. The split exists so I can see context at a glance and revoke any address that starts attracting spam.
  </p>

  <h2>Response time</h2>
  <p>
    Usually within 48 hours for research and clinical contacts. Other things may take longer if I'm deep in a sprint. No SLA — this is one person, not a company.
  </p>

  <h2>What I'm interested in</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Collaboration on Hebrew NLP, ulpan pedagogy research, or open-source learning tools.</li>
    <li>Clinical or lab contacts working on pediatric undiagnosed disease — particularly anyone running rare phenotypes through GeneMatcher / Matchmaker Exchange.</li>
    <li>Critique. If you spot a methodological flaw in something I've written or shipped, I want to know.</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
